text: The Manrique snouted tree frog (Scinax manriquei) is a frog. It lives in Venezuela and Colombia. It lives in the lower parts of the Andes mountains, between 1400 and 1700 meters above sea level. This frog is yellow in color. It has two stripes on its back. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax manriquei
